                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion4" href="#collapse1four4">
                                    Is any maintenance needed for my solar PV system? How often should solar panels be cleaned? 
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapse1four4" class="accordion-body collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>With limited maintenance, your solar system will operate at peak performance for many years. Cleaning intervals will vary depending on site-specific factors such as annual rainfall, roof tilt (some arrays mounted at steep tilt angles in locations with hard rains will somewhat self-clean), and proximity of factors causing dust or debris on the array (such as trees or a frequently-traveled dirt road). On an average once in a month cleaning of solar PV modules can be done. <br><br>It is best to consult your solar installer for a recommended cleaning schedule. AHA Rooftop Solar Helper recommends annual servicing to inspect electrical and mechanical connections for cleanliness, tightness, possible damage, and to ensure that the PV system is operating properly. </p>
